$interpreted: Alliance Soldier: The match is about to begin, if you’d all come with me—
Puggi: Pang~ Did you miss me!?
Alliance Soldier: Hey! You can’t just waltz right in here!
Puggi: Pang~!! Did you hear? I’m the Alliance Beauty!

Pang: I’ve brought you the artisan, so please do your part.
Let the insect princess win.
Ace: ...Why are you helping her?
Pang: ...I owe her one.
Ace: ...I’ll keep my word.
Puggi: ...Uh oh, something’s not right!
Puggi: My MC sense is tingling, there’s a problem here...
Jia-Shen: What’s wrong?
Puggi: It’s Pang! Ever since he came back from Hot Spring Street, he’s been all weird and gloomy.
Puggi: What if he threw all his money away at the guesthouses, and now he’s in debt with the wrong kind of people!?
Jia-Shen: Eh... I don’t think he’s the type to do that.
Jia-Shen: But you’re right, he does seem like he’s got somethin’ on his mind.
Jia-Shen: Ah, right!
Jia-Shen: I’ve got a little something here that should perk Pang’s spirits right up.

Jia-Shen: This stuff’s pretty strong, though.
Dunno if Pang can handle it...
Puggi: What!? That sounds super dangerous!!
Puggi: And I love danger!
Chiyuki: For this match, we ask every contestant to wear a fog pearl.
Chiyuki: Also, Sir Ace, diplomat from the Kingdom of the Sun will be joining in!
Chiyuki: Contestants, you'll have to pay attention and make sure to dodge any of Ace’s attacks!
Pang: (All this fog, I can’t see a thing other than this shining pearl.)
Pang: (Ace must be aiming for this pearl.)
Himawari: Damn! This fog is just getting heavier and heavier!
Soohyeon: It’s getting harder and harder to see, my eyes are starting to hurt!
Pang: (Everyone seems to be equally affected by this fog.)
Chiyuki: Soohyeon of the Kyo Tribe and Himawari of the Leopard Tribe are both out!!!
Himawari: Damn! Damndamndamn!!

Soohyeon: Ace is way too fast, and this fog is way too dense!
I have no idea what direction he’s coming from!
Toyokuni: They think this fog can hold me back? I’m a mythic of the Fog Sect itself! This is nothing to me!
Tindoiimu: Can't be much longer...
Pang: (Soohyeon and Himawari are both out... I must be next.)
Pang: (Alright, time to stop messing around. Let’s do this!)
Pang: (What was that noise? Two more broken fog pearls? ...Is it over?)
Chiyuki: Toyokuni of the Komainu Tribe and Tindoiimu of the Qilin Tribe are disqualified!
Pang: What!?
Tindoiimu: ...Agh...
Toyokuni: ...I was too careless…
Ace: Make way!
Chiyuki: Let’s give a big round of applause to the victor, Pang!! He’s got a guaranteed spot in the finals!
Chiyuki: The next event will take place in Fei-Hua City! As per the drawing last time, the two teams will consist of Toyokuni and Soohyeon...
Chiyuki: ...and Himawari and Tindoiimu!
Chiyuki: Then the victors from the two teams will battle it out again, with the final victor squaring off against Pang in the finals!
Chiyuki: Oh yes, get excited indeed! It’ll be a doozy! Well, this is Hanazono Chiyuki, signing off! Have a great day, everybody!
Pang: Why the hell...!? I thought your word was your bond!?
Ace: ...And it is.
Pang: Then why the hell did you let me—
Ace: The one who gave me info on the artisan told me to let you win.
Pang: Huh...?
Ace: Sorry, someone else beat you to the punch.
Pang: ...Yao!!

Pang: Then what was all that about past memories...? 
It was all a lie...
